Japan Life Insurers to Waive Natural Disaster Exemption, Pay Full Benefits

-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 
2011-03-15T23:00:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/japan-life-insurers-to-waive-natural-disaster-exemption-pay-full-benefits.html
  Japan ’s life insurance association
said all insurers will waive natural disaster exemptions and pay
benifits in full following the March 11 earthquake and tsunami.
The disaster may have killed more than 10,000 people. The
statement, dated March 15, was posted on the association’s
website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
